# vibe-tools

vibe-tools is a CLI tool installed on this machine. Use it for advanced tasks.

## Key Commands

**Repository Analysis (uses Gemini):**
`vibe-tools repo "<question>" [--subdir=<path>] [--from-github=<user/repo>]`

**Web Search (uses Perplexity):**
`vibe-tools web "<question>"` — ask natural language questions, not keyword searches

**Implementation Planning (multi-model):**
`vibe-tools plan "<task description>"` — identifies relevant files, generates detailed plan

**Documentation Generation:**
`vibe-tools doc [--output=<file>]`

**Browser Automation (Stagehand):**
`vibe-tools browser open "<url>" [--html] [--screenshot=<file>]`
`vibe-tools browser act "<action>" --url=<url>`
`vibe-tools browser extract "<what>" --url=<url>`

**GitHub:**
`vibe-tools github pr [number]` — get PRs
`vibe-tools github issue [number]` — get issues

**YouTube Analysis:**
`vibe-tools youtube "<url>" [--type=summary|transcript|plan]`

**MCP Server Tools:**
`vibe-tools mcp search "<query>"` — find MCP servers
`vibe-tools mcp run "<query>"` — execute MCP tools

## Important Rules

- For specific URLs, always use `--with-doc=<url>` instead of `web` command
- `web` uses natural language questions — never keyword-style queries
- `repo` is best for codebase-specific questions, reviews, and debugging
- `plan` is best for implementation planning tasks
- Browser commands are stateless unless using `--connect-to`
- API keys are loaded from `~/.vibe-tools/.env`

## Common Options

- `--provider=<name>` — openai, anthropic, perplexity, gemini, openrouter, xai, groq
- `--model=<name>` — override default model
- `--max-tokens=<n>` — control response length
- `--save-to=<file>` — save output to file
- `--with-doc=<url>` — include URL content as context (can repeat)
- `--debug` — show detailed logs
